               <p>"This is the last will and testament of me Thomas Sawtell, late of Saffron-hill, in the parish of St. Andrew, Holborn, in the county of Middlesex, tallow-chandler, but now of Brook-street, in the said parish of St. Andrew, Holborn, in the said county of Middlesex, gentleman. First, I will, order, and direct, that all my just debts be paid and discharged as soon as conveniently may be, after my decease, by my executors hereinafter named; I give and bequeath to my sister 
