                     <interp inst="t17860111-2-person173" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , lived with him to his last dying moments, and was<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="178601110026"></xptr> very much benefitted in the real will, as well as in the false one; I see a considerable legacy is left to him, as well as 
               <persName id="t17860111-2-person174">
                  Elizabeth
                   Spraggs
               <interp inst="t17860111-2-person174" type="surname" value="Spraggs"></interp>
